Class SimpleSymbol

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.document.SimpleSymbol
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Symbol

    public class SimpleSymbol
extends java.lang.Object
implements Symbol
    A simple symbol that directly stores the type and value

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static SimpleSymbol PLACEHOLDER
      A special symbol used as a placeholder by symbol providers that only want to note the existence of a symbol.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      SimpleSymbol(IType type, java.lang.Object value)
      Creates a simple symbol with the explicitly given type and value
      SimpleSymbol(java.lang.Object value)
      Creates a simple symbol from a value, deriving the type from the value, except a null value gets the type for Object and if the value is a Symbol, the type and value from that symbol are copied instead.
